						               													<description>In Super-GAUdi each player is a boss of an nuclear energy company. Each player starts with 7 barrels full of atomic waste and has to put them to one of the final storages on the playing schedule. The player that gets rid of all his barrels at first, wins the game. The clue is, that the players can either put a barrel to one of the hidden final storages or they can look if a final storage is safe or note safe. During the game each players knows some safe and some unsafe storages. After a player put a barrel with atomic waste to one of the final storage-cards, the other players can say that they don't believe that this final storage is safe. If they are right, the player has to take all the barrels on this card (up to three). If he was honest, he gives one of his barrels to the player that distrusted him.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Flavor text:&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Die Gesch&amp;auml;fte laufen wie geschmiert, doch die Chefs der gro&amp;szlig;en Atomkonzerne haben ein Problem: Sie wissen nicht wohin mit dem ganzen Atomm&amp;uuml;ll. Es gilt also endlich ein &amp;quot;Endlager&amp;quot; zu finden, auf Teufel komm raus! Sei es ein gammeliges Bergwerk, ein Naturschutzgebiet oder der K&amp;uuml;hlschrank von Mutti - no Risk, no Fun! Bleibt nur zu hoffen, dass der Bluff nicht auffliegt... Gewonnen hat derjenige Atomboss, der seinen ganzen Atomm&amp;uuml;ll als Erster los ist.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
